# TypeScript

- Always implement in the easiest, most straightforward way possible
- Avoid unnecessary complexity
- Always use proper types, avoid using `any` at all costs, avoid casting types using `as` at all costs
- Always type your state definitions
- Never use `@ts-expect-error` without asking the user
- Always `Boolean()` instead of `!!` for boolean coercion
- Always use `async` and `await` instead of legacy promises
- Always use static imports at the top of the file instead of dynamic `import()` calls unless there's a specific performance or code-splitting requirement